<paragraph id="790D910EF623FFE5AB1795D0FC30FCA5" blockId="2.[811,1421,361,1649]" pageId="2" pageNumber="325">
<emphasis id="4BC64D1CF623FFE5AB1795D0FAE5FD95" box="[813,1386,501,525]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="325" reason="1">
<emphasis id="4BC64D1CF623FFE5AB1795D0FC5DFD95" bold="true" box="[813,978,501,525]" pageId="2" pageNumber="325">Identification.</emphasis>
This species is easily identified as
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="BEB2EA8DF623FFE5AD4C95D3FC1EFDB7" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Hymenochaetaceae" genus="Fomitiporia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hymenochaetales" pageId="2" pageNumber="325" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="apiahyna">
<emphasis id="4BC64D1CF623FFE5AD4C95D3FA02FD95" box="[1398,1421,502,525]" inLineHeading="true" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="325" reason="1">F.</emphasis>
apiahyna
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="50F5F067F623FFE5ABAD9632FC39FDB7" box="[919,950,535,559]" pageId="2" pageNumber="325" sensu="lato">s.l.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by the following characters: basidiome perennial, ungulate (
<figureCitation id="E1898D8BF623FFE5ABC2961CFBC2FDC9" box="[1016,1101,569,593]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="3.[168,231,1954,1974]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,160,1930]" captionTargetId="figure-6@3.[168,1419,160,1933]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 2. Macroscopic structures (hymenophore, pileal region, pores of hymenophore, tubes and context). A. Fomitiporia apiahynat. B. F. calkinsii. C. F. conyana. D. F.impercepta." pageId="2" pageNumber="325">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
) with hymenophoral surface and pores circular to angular, 5–7 per mm (
<figureCitation id="E1898D8BF623FFE5ACCD967FFAC5FDEB" box="[1271,1354,602,627]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="3.[168,231,1954,1974]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,160,1930]" captionTargetId="figure-6@3.[168,1419,160,1933]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 2. Macroscopic structures (hymenophore, pileal region, pores of hymenophore, tubes and context). A. Fomitiporia apiahynat. B. F. calkinsii. C. F. conyana. D. F.impercepta." pageId="2" pageNumber="325">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
); context woody, yellowish brown (
<figureCitation id="E1898D8BF623FFE5AC459659FB59FD0C" box="[1151,1238,636,660]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="3.[168,231,1954,1974]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,160,1930]" captionTargetId="figure-6@3.[168,1419,160,1933]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 2. Macroscopic structures (hymenophore, pileal region, pores of hymenophore, tubes and context). A. Fomitiporia apiahynat. B. F. calkinsii. C. F. conyana. D. F.impercepta." pageId="2" pageNumber="325">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
); hyphal system dimitic, with generative hyphae hyaline, thin-walled, septate (
<figureCitation id="E1898D8BF623FFE5ABB096E5FC6EFD40" box="[906,993,704,728]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="6.[169,232,1980,2000]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,187,1931]" captionTargetId="figure-13@6.[169,1419,184,1933]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 4. Microscopic structures (generative hyphae - left; skeletal hyphae - right; basidiospores). A. Fomitiporia apiahyna. B. F. calkinsii. C. F. conyana. D. F. impercepta. E. F. langloisii. F.F. maxonii. G. F.murrillii. H. F.neotropica." pageId="2" pageNumber="325">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
); skeletal hyphae abundant, yellowish, thick-walled, nonseptate (
<figureCitation id="E1898D8BF623FFE5AC7896C4FB19FD61" box="[1090,1174,737,761]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="6.[169,232,1980,2000]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,187,1931]" captionTargetId="figure-13@6.[169,1419,184,1933]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 4. Microscopic structures (generative hyphae - left; skeletal hyphae - right; basidiospores). A. Fomitiporia apiahyna. B. F. calkinsii. C. F. conyana. D. F. impercepta. E. F. langloisii. F.F. maxonii. G. F.murrillii. H. F.neotropica." pageId="2" pageNumber="325">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
); basidiospores dextrinoid, subglobose, hyaline, thick-walled, 6–7.5 × 5.8–6 μm (
<figureCitation id="E1898D8BF623FFE5AB659700FC3CFCA5" box="[863,947,805,829]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="6.[169,232,1980,2000]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,187,1931]" captionTargetId="figure-13@6.[169,1419,184,1933]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 4. Microscopic structures (generative hyphae - left; skeletal hyphae - right; basidiospores). A. Fomitiporia apiahyna. B. F. calkinsii. C. F. conyana. D. F. impercepta. E. F. langloisii. F.F. maxonii. G. F.murrillii. H. F.neotropica." pageId="2" pageNumber="325">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="31A8C285F623FFE5AB179769FB96FAE7" pageId="2" pageNumber="325" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="790D910EF623FFE5AB179769FB96FAE7" blockId="2.[811,1421,361,1649]" pageId="2" pageNumber="325">
<emphasis id="4BC64D1CF623FFE5AB179769FCD6FC1D" inLineHeading="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="325" reason="1">
<emphasis id="4BC64D1CF623FFE5AB179769FC2CFCFC" bold="true" box="[813,931,844,868]" pageId="2" pageNumber="325">Remarks..</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="BEB2EA8DF623FFE5AB949768FB2EFCFC" box="[942,1185,844,868]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Hymenochaetaceae" genus="Fomitiporia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hymenochaetales" pageId="2" pageNumber="325" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="apiahyna">
<emphasis id="4BC64D1CF623FFE5AB949768FB2EFCFC" box="[942,1185,844,868]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="325">Fomitiporia apiahyna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a worldwide species
</emphasis>
, but curiously there are few records in Neotropics (
<bibRefCitation id="1D23ECFFF623FFE5AB0E97AAFC69FC3F" author="Ryvarden, L" box="[820,998,911,935]" pageId="2" pageNumber="325" refId="ref6163" refString="Ryvarden, L (2004) Neotropical Polypores, part 1: introduction, Hymenochaetaceae and Ganodermataceae. Synopsis fungorum, volume 9. Fungiflora, Oslo, Norway, 227 pp." type="book" year="2004">Ryvarden 2004</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="1D23ECFFF623FFE5ABC797AAFAAEFC3F" author="Alves-Silva G &amp; Reck MA &amp; Silveira RMB &amp; Bittencourt F &amp; Robledo GL &amp; Goes-Neto A &amp; Drechsler-Santos ER" box="[1021,1313,911,935]" pageId="2" pageNumber="325" pagination="769 - 790" refId="ref4835" refString="Alves-Silva G, Reck MA, Silveira RMB, Bittencourt F, Robledo GL, Goes-Neto A, Drechsler-Santos ER (2020 b) The Neotropical Fomitiporia (Hymenochaetales, Basidiomycota): the redefinition of F. apiahyna s. s. allows revealing a high hidden species diversity. Mycological Progress 19: 769 - 790. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 11557 - 020 - 01593 - 5" type="journal article" year="2020">Alves-Silva et al. (2020b)</bibRefCitation>
corroborated this hypothesis and found that the geographical distributions of species in this complex are extremely important in their classification. 
<taxonomicName id="BEB2EA8DF623FFE5ACA697D0FA03FB94" box="[1180,1420,1012,1036]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Hymenochaetaceae" genus="Fomitiporia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hymenochaetales" pageId="2" pageNumber="325" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="apiahyna">
<emphasis id="4BC64D1CF623FFE5ACA697D0FA03FB94" box="[1180,1420,1012,1036]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="325">Fomitiporia apiahyna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis id="4BC64D1CF623FFE5AB0F9032FC31FBB6" box="[821,958,1047,1070]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="325">sensu stricto</emphasis>
) is not part of the clade of species in the Amazon region; it is restricted to Araucária Moist Forest ecoregion. Our specimens have a basidiospores that are larger on average (6–7.5 × 5.8–6 μm) than in 
<taxonomicName id="BEB2EA8DF623FFE5AD2E9059FA04FB0B" authorityName="Alves-Silva &amp; Drechsler-Santos" authorityYear="2020" box="[1300,1419,1148,1171]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Hymenochaetaceae" genus="Fomitiporia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hymenochaetales" pageId="2" pageNumber="325" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="conyana">
<emphasis id="4BC64D1CF623FFE5AD2E9059FA04FB0B" box="[1300,1419,1148,1171]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="325">F. conyana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(5–5.5 × 4–5 μm), 
<taxonomicName id="BEB2EA8DF623FFE5ABC590BBFBF7FB2D" authorityName="Alves-Silva, R. M. Silveira &amp; Drechsler-Santos" authorityYear="2020" box="[1023,1144,1181,1205]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Hymenochaetaceae" genus="Fomitiporia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hymenochaetales" pageId="2" pageNumber="325" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="murrillii">
<emphasis id="4BC64D1CF623FFE5ABC590BBFBF7FB2D" box="[1023,1144,1181,1205]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="325">F. murrillii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(5–6 × 5–6), and 
<taxonomicName id="BEB2EA8DF623FFE5AD7290BBFCFFFB4F" authorityName="Alves-Silva, Bittencourt &amp; Drechsler-Santos" authorityYear="2020" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Hymenochaetaceae" genus="Fomitiporia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hymenochaetales" pageId="2" pageNumber="325" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="nubicola">
<emphasis id="4BC64D1CF623FFE5AD7290BBFCFFFB4F" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="325">F. nubicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(5–6 × 5–6). Thus, we classify our specimens as 
<emphasis id="4BC64D1CF623FFE5AB1490C4FC48FB60" box="[814,967,1248,1272]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="325">
<taxonomicName id="BEB2EA8DF623FFE5AB1490C4FC2DFB60" box="[814,930,1249,1272]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Hymenochaetaceae" genus="Fomitiporia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hymenochaetales" pageId="2" pageNumber="325" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="apiayna">F. apiayna</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="50F5F067F623FFE5AB9090C5FC48FB60" box="[938,967,1248,1272]" pageId="2" pageNumber="325" sensu="lato">s.l.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, as 
<emphasis id="4BC64D1CF623FFE5ABC990C4FB1EFB60" box="[1011,1169,1249,1272]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="325">
<taxonomicName id="BEB2EA8DF623FFE5ABC990C4FBE8FB60" box="[1011,1127,1249,1272]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Hymenochaetaceae" genus="Fomitiporia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hymenochaetales" pageId="2" pageNumber="325" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="apiayna">F. apiayna</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="50F5F067F623FFE5AC5490C4FB1EFB60" box="[1134,1169,1249,1272]" pageId="2" pageNumber="325" sensu="stricto">s.s.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is not part of the clade containing Amazonian species. Our specimens may rep- resent a distinct lineage and potentially a new species in the complex, but phylogenetic studies are needed to prove this hypothesis.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="31A8C285F623FFE5AB1791ABFBB6F9E8" pageId="2" pageNumber="325" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="790D910EF623FFE5AB1791ABFBB6F9E8" blockId="2.[811,1421,361,1649]" pageId="2" pageNumber="325">
