<taxonomicNameLabel id="50F5F067F623FFE5ACF491ABFB62FA3E" box="[1230,1261,1422,1446]" pageId="2" pageNumber="325" sensu="lato">s.l.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
was reported
</emphasis>
from southern 
<collectingCountry id="01A5D19EF623FFE5ABDA9195FBAAFA50" box="[992,1061,1456,1480]" name="Brazil" pageId="2" pageNumber="325">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="01A5D19EF623FFE5AC009195FB25FA50" box="[1082,1194,1456,1480]" name="Argentina" pageId="2" pageNumber="325">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="01A5D19EF623FFE5AC849195FA95FA50" box="[1214,1306,1456,1480]" name="Ecuador" pageId="2" pageNumber="325">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="01A5D19EF623FFE5AD159194FA07FA50" box="[1327,1416,1457,1480]" name="Panama" pageId="2" pageNumber="325">Panama</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="01A5D19EF623FFE5AB1791F7FC24FA72" box="[813,939,1490,1514]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="2" pageNumber="325">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="01A5D19EF623FFE5AB8391F7FB82FA72" box="[953,1037,1490,1514]" name="Mexico" pageId="2" pageNumber="325">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, and Florida (
<bibRefCitation id="1D23ECFFF623FFE5AC9591F7FCECF994" author="Amalfi M &amp; Decock C" pageId="2" pageNumber="325" pagination="873 - 887" refId="ref4911" refString="Amalfi M, Decock C (2013) Fomitiporia castilloi sp. nov. and multiple clades around F. apiahyna and F. texana in Meso- and South America evidenced by multiloci phylogenetic inferences. Mycologia 105 (4): 873 - 887. https: // doi. org / 10.3852 / 11 - 423" type="journal article" year="2013">Amalfi and Decock 2013</bibRefCitation>
). According 
<bibRefCitation id="1D23ECFFF623FFE5ABD691D1FA87F994" author="Amalfi M &amp; Decock C" box="[1004,1288,1524,1548]" pageId="2" pageNumber="325" pagination="873 - 887" refId="ref4911" refString="Amalfi M, Decock C (2013) Fomitiporia castilloi sp. nov. and multiple clades around F. apiahyna and F. texana in Meso- and South America evidenced by multiloci phylogenetic inferences. Mycologia 105 (4): 873 - 887. https: // doi. org / 10.3852 / 11 - 423" type="journal article" year="2013">Amalfi and Decock (2013)</bibRefCitation>
there is one record in the Amazon region, in French Guiana. However 
<bibRefCitation id="1D23ECFFF623FFE5AB5A9212FBE1F9D7" author="Alves-Silva G &amp; Reck MA &amp; Silveira RMB &amp; Bittencourt F &amp; Robledo GL &amp; Goes-Neto A &amp; Drechsler-Santos ER" box="[864,1134,1591,1615]" pageId="2" pageNumber="325" pagination="769 - 790" refId="ref4835" refString="Alves-Silva G, Reck MA, Silveira RMB, Bittencourt F, Robledo GL, Goes-Neto A, Drechsler-Santos ER (2020 b) The Neotropical Fomitiporia (Hymenochaetales, Basidiomycota): the redefinition of F. apiahyna s. s. allows revealing a high hidden species diversity. Mycological Progress 19: 769 - 790. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 11557 - 020 - 01593 - 5" type="journal article" year="2020">Alves-Silva et al. (2020b)</bibRefCitation>
had shown that this record was actually 
<taxonomicName id="BEB2EA8DF623FFE5AB80927FFBBDF9E9" authorityName="Alves-Silva &amp; Drechsler-Santos" authorityYear="2020" box="[954,1074,1626,1649]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Hymenochaetaceae" genus="Fomitiporia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hymenochaetales" pageId="2" pageNumber="325" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="conyana">
<emphasis id="4BC64D1CF623FFE5AB80927FFBBDF9E9" box="[954,1074,1626,1649]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="325">F. conyana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
